/**
 * ============================================================================
 * WHAT IS AN ENTERPRISE APPLICATION?
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * An Enterprise Application is a large-scale software system designed to support
 * complex business processes and operations of an organization. These applications
 * handle critical business functions and are essential for day-to-day operations.
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * BANKING SERVICES OVERVIEW
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * 1. Core Banking Services:
 *    - Savings Account Management
 *    - Current Account Management
 *    - Fixed Deposits
 *    - Recurring Deposits
 * 
 * 2. Lending Services:
 *    - Home Loans
 *    - Car Loans
 *    - Personal Loans
 *    - Education Loans
 *    - Business Loans
 * 
 * 3. Investment Services:
 *    - Mutual Funds
 *    - Stocks Trading
 *    - Bonds
 *    - Insurance Products
 * 
 * 4. Digital Banking:
 *    - Internet Banking
 *    - Mobile Banking
 *    - SMS Banking
 *    - Phone Banking
 *    - ATM Services
 * 
 * 5. Payment Services:
 *    - NEFT/RTGS/IMPS
 *    - UPI Payments
 *    - Bill Payments
 *    - Credit Card Payments
 * 
 * 6. Customer Services:
 *    - Customer Relationship Management
 *    - Complaint Management
 *    - Service Requests
 *    - Feedback Management
 * 
 * 7. Branch Operations:
 *    - Teller Services
 *    - Cash Management
 *    - Cheque Processing
 *    - Account Opening
 * 
 * 8. Backend Operations:
 *    - Batch Processing
 *    - EMI Processing
 *    - Interest Calculation
 *    - Reconciliation
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * MONOLITHIC SERVICES
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * Definition: A monolithic application is built as a single unified unit where
 * all components are tightly coupled and deployed together.
 * 
 * Characteristics:
 * - Single codebase
 * - Single deployment unit (EAR/WAR)
 * - Shared database
 * - Single technology stack
 * 
 * Drawbacks:
 * 1. Single Point of Failure: If one component fails, entire application fails
 * 2. Scaling Difficult: Can only scale the entire application
 * 3. Technology Lock-in: Cannot use different technologies for different components
 * 4. Development Bottleneck: Large teams working on same codebase
 * 5. Deployment Risk: Any change requires redeploying entire application
 * 6. Performance Issues: Memory leak in one service affects all services
 * 
 * Real-World Example - Bank Monolith:
 * - Account Service
 * - Loan Service
 * - Insurance Service
 * - Payment Service
 * - All packaged in single WAR file
 * - Deployed on a single application server
 * - If Account Service has memory leak, all services become slow/unavailable
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * MICROSERVICES ARCHITECTURE
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * Definition: Microservices is an architectural style that structures an application
 * as a collection of loosely coupled, independently deployable services.
 * 
 * Characteristics:
 * - Each service runs independently
 * - Each service has its own database
 * - Services communicate via APIs
 * - Polyglot architecture (different tech stacks)
 * - Independently deployable
 * - Organized around business capabilities
 * 
 * Advantages:
 * 1. Independent Deployment: Each service can be deployed independently
 * 2. Scalability: Scale only services that need scaling
 * 3. Fault Isolation: Failure in one service doesn't affect others
 * 4. Technology Diversity: Use best technology for each service
 * 5. Team Autonomy: Teams can own and manage specific services
 * 6. Continuous Delivery: Easier to implement CI/CD
 * 7. Easier Debugging: Issues are isolated to specific services
 * 8. Improved Availability: Services can be restarted independently
 * 
 * Challenges:
 * 1. Distributed System Complexity
 * 2. Network Latency and Faults
 * 3. Data Consistency
 * 4. Distributed Transactions
 * 5. Service Discovery
 * 6. API Gateway Required
 * 7. Monitoring and Logging Complexity
 * 8. Testing Complexity
 * 9. Security Challenges
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * MONOLITHIC VS MICROSERVICES - COMPARISON
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * Aspect          | Monolithic                 | Microservices
 * ----------------|---------------------------|-------------------------------
 * Deployment      | Single unit               | Multiple independent units
 * Scaling         | Scale entire app          | Scale individual services
 * Development     | Single codebase           | Multiple codebases
 * Technology      | Single stack              | Multiple stacks
 * Team Structure  | Large team                | Small, focused teams
 * Database        | Shared database           | Database per service
 * Communication   | In-memory calls           | Network calls (REST/Message)
 * Fault Tolerance | Single point of failure   | Isolated failures
 * Deployment      | Slow, risky               | Fast, independent
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * BANKING SCENARIO - BEFORE AND AFTER MICROSERVICES
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * BEFORE (Monolithic):
 * - All services in single WAR file
 * - Festival shopping causes high volume on account balance service
 * - Memory leak in account balance service
 * - Entire application becomes unresponsive
 * - Loan applications fail
 * - Insurance processing fails
 * - Customer service cannot process credit card reports
 * - Server restart required, 2-3 hours downtime
 * 
 * AFTER (Microservices):
 * - Account service, Loan service, Insurance service separate
 * - Festival shopping affects only Account service
 * - Loan and Insurance services continue working
 * - Customers can still submit loan applications
 * - Insurance processing continues
 * - Customer service can report stolen cards
 * - Only Account service needs restart
 * - No downtime for other services
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * SERVICE DISCOVERY (EUREKA)
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * What is Service Discovery?
 * - Mechanism for services to find each other
 * - Services register themselves with Discovery Server
 * - Clients query Discovery Server to find services
 * - Enables dynamic scaling
 * 
 * Eureka Server:
 * - Netflix's service discovery server
 * - Maintains registry of available services
 * - Services register with Eureka on startup
 * - Heartbeats maintain service availability
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 * API GATEWAY
 * ============================================================================
 * 
 * What is API Gateway?
 * - Single entry point for all clients
 * - Routes requests to appropriate microservices
 * - Handles cross-cutting concerns:
 *   - Authentication/Authorization
 *   - Rate Limiting
 *   - Caching
 *   - Request/Response Transformation
 *   - Logging
 *   - Metrics
 * 
 * Benefits:
 * - Simplifies client code
 * - Reduces number of requests
 * - Implements security policies
 * - Enables protocol translation
 * - Provides centralized monitoring
 * 
 * ============================================================================
 */

